      "writtenOn": "2026-06-23T11:43:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This change is not to encourage manual edits of a system-managed file. It makes restore parsing more robust when comment or blank lines appear before the forwarding rule (for example from provisioning/config tooling).\n\nPreviously, parsing assumed the rule was on the first line, which could cause restore to fall back to defaults. This fix skips comment/blank lines and parses the first valid entry, while keeping the file management model unchanged.",
